Suggest using modern nested namespace declaration:

```
namespace phosphor::health::metric::config
{
}
```

This is an example where I'd rather have something like the following if you're just trying to avoid magics.

```
constexpr auto collectionFrequency = ...;
 healthMetricConfig.collectionFrequency = jsonObj.value(collectionFrequency, ...);
```

Having to bounce all around the file when reviewing is more work.
